Former Devolution PS Peter Mangiti has recounted ordeals that may have led to the Sh791 million National Youth Service scam.Appearing before National Assembly PAC on Wednesday, Mangiti gave at least ten shocking revelations.The former PS was charged with trying to cover up a conspiracy to defraud the NYS of Sh695.4 million.He was accused alongside other suspects of threatening and intimidating former NYS deputy general Adan Harakhe with consequences.The committee questioned Mangiti following a session on Tuesday with key suspect, Nairobi businesswoman Josephine Kabura.Read: Kabura tells PAC she owns, solely runs 20 companies in NYS probe